rename the clusters based on levels

cluster_domain are provided by reval as numeric lables. We then convert them to a verbal/descriptive label:

  • 2= high
  • 3= med
  • 1 = low
for (i in (1:length(data$cluster_domain))) {
  if (data[i, 'cluster_domain'] == '2'){
    data[i,'clust_dom'] = "high"
  }
  else if (data[i, 'cluster_domain'] == '3'){
    data[i,'clust_dom'] = "med"
  }
  else if (data[i, 'cluster_domain'] == '1'){
    data[i,'clust_dom'] = "low"
  }
}

# make the cluster column as a factor
data$clust_dom = as.factor(data$clust_dom)
data$clust_dom <- factor( data$clust_dom,levels = c('high','med','low'));

produce scatter plot for the input features - VABS domain standard scores

plot heatmap of Cohens d

heat = list()

for (i in (1:4) ){
  var2use = var_list[i]
  print(var2use)
  color = col_list[[i]]
  title = title_list[i]
  
  vector <- c()
  index <- 0
  group_order <- c("high", "med","low")
  # compute cohens'd
  for (A in group_order){
    for (B in group_order){
      index <- index + 1
      C_d <- cohens_d(data2use[data2use$clust_dom==A,var2use],
                      data2use[data2use$clust_dom==B,var2use], 
                      SIGN=FALSE)
      vector[index] <- round(C_d,digits=2)
    }}
  
  m = matrix(vector,3)
  print(m)
  
  ggheatmap = ggplot(melt(m), aes(Var1,Var2, fill=value)) + 
    scale_x_discrete(name="Vabs_clus",limits=c(1,2,3),labels=c("low", "med","high")) + 
    scale_y_discrete(name="Vabs_clus",limits =c(1,2,3),labels=c("low", "med","high")) + 
    geom_raster() +
    scale_fill_gradient2(low = color[4], high = color[1],  limit = c(0,4), guide = "colourbar",name=NULL) +
    theme_minimal()#+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank())#element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, 
  #size = 14, hjust = 1)) +
  #coord_fixed()
  
  ggheatmap = ggheatmap +
    geom_text(aes(Var1, Var2, label = value), color = "black", size = 25) +
    theme(
      axis.title.x = element_blank(),
      axis.title.y = element_blank(),
      panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
      panel.border = element_blank(),
      panel.background = element_blank(),
      axis.ticks = element_blank())+
    guides(fill = guide_colorbar(barwidth = 1, barheight = 10,
                                 title.position = "top", title.hjust = 0, title="d"))
  
  # show here the heatmaps to check them
  #print(ggheatmap)
  # eventually save them on a pdf file
  # ggsave(paste(plot_path,'/',db_type,'_heatmap_',var2use,".pdf", sep=""),width = 10,height = 9)
  heat[[i]]=ggheatmap
}

plot REVAL stability plot

# read reval output
reval_val = read.csv(file.path(data_path,"val_metric_P14soggettti.csv"))
reval_val$cat = 'validation'
reval_tr = read.csv(file.path(data_path,"train_metric_P14soggettti.csv"))
reval_tr$cat = 'train'

# plot them
mat = rbind(reval_tr,reval_val)
colors = c("#cc0000","#000099")
# spaghetti plot
gg.spaghetti_x<-ggplot(mat, aes (x = k, y =value , group = cat, color = cat))
gg.spaghetti_x <-gg.spaghetti_x +geom_line() + geom_point()   +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin= value - CI, ymax= value + CI), width = 0.1, size = 0.5) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size=10), axis.text.y = element_text(size=10)) +
  scale_color_manual(values=colors)+theme_classic()

## check clusters existence
library(sigclust)
library(dplyr)

library(ggplot2)
library(wesanderson)

# VABS data
data <- read.csv("~/OneDrive - Fondazione Istituto Italiano Tecnologia/vineland_proj_new/results/FINAL_correct/ndar_withumap.csv", header=TRUE)
color =  wes_palette("IsleofDogs1")
# set option
nreps_sim = 10000
nreps_sigclust_repeat = 10000

data$cluster_domain =factor(data$cluster_domain, levels = c("2",'3','1'))
# run sigclust on train
data2use = data %>% filter(TR_TS=="tr") %>% select(UMAP_1,UMAP_2,cluster_domain)
rseo_sigclust_res_train = sigclust(data2use[,c("UMAP_1","UMAP_2")],
                             nsim = nreps_sim, nrep = nreps_sigclust_repeat,
                             labflag = 1, 
                             label = data2use[,"cluster_domain"],
                             icovest=2)
p_train = ggplot(data=data2use, aes(x=UMAP_1,y=UMAP_2)) +
    geom_density_2d_filled() + 
    geom_point(data=data2use, aes(colour=cluster_domain), alpha = 0.5,size = 0.5)+ggtitle('train')+ 
    scale_y_continuous( limits=c(-5, 1)) + scale_x_continuous( limits=c(-5,8))+ scale_colour_manual(values = color)
p_train

#rseo_sigclust_res_train
p_val_train = (sum(rseo_sigclust_res_train@simcindex<=rseo_sigclust_res_train@xcindex)+1)/(nreps_sim+1)
print(p_val_train)
## [1] 9.999e-05
# run sigclust on test
data2use = data %>% filter(TR_TS=="ts") %>% select(UMAP_1,UMAP_2,cluster_domain)
rseo_sigclust_res_test = sigclust(data2use[,c("UMAP_1","UMAP_2")],
                             nsim = nreps_sim, nrep = nreps_sigclust_repeat,
                             labflag = 1, 
                             label = data2use[,"cluster_domain"],
                             icovest=2)
p_test = ggplot(data=data2use, aes(x=UMAP_1,y=UMAP_2)) +
    geom_density_2d_filled() + 
    geom_point(data=data2use, aes(colour=cluster_domain), alpha = 0.5,size = 0.5)+ggtitle('validation')+ 
    scale_y_continuous( limits=c(-5, 1)) + scale_x_continuous( limits=c(-5, 8))+ scale_colour_manual(values = color)
p_test

#rseo_sigclust_res_test
p_val_test = (sum(rseo_sigclust_res_test@simcindex<=rseo_sigclust_res_test@xcindex)+1)/(nreps_sim+1)
print(p_val_test)
## [1] 9.999e-05
library(ggpubr)
umap_tr_ts = ggarrange(p_train, p_test, nrow=1, common.legend = TRUE, legend="bottom")
umap_tr_ts
